I'd like to see void be usable as a valid type for a template parameter,
so that generated functions could include void among their possible
return types.

I'd also like to see "void" be usable as the type of an external
identifier, meaning that the identifier refers to something at some
address whose type is unknown. The only thing you'd be able to do with
the identifier would be to take its address, which would naturally be of
type void*.

