The standard defines offsetof, which nicely complements sizeof. I'd like
to see lengthof added to the standard, which would return the number of
elements in an array:

	#define lengthof(x) (sizeof(x) / sizeof(*(x)))

It is obviously undefined for some arguments, and produces meaningless
results for others, but the same is true for offsetof.

